---
import TerminalPage from '../../layouts/TerminalPage.astro';

const systems = [
  ['Tencent Cloud', 'Public cloud container platform architecture, AI infrastructure, resource scheduling, and GPU virtualization systems.'],
  ['TalkingData', 'Cloud-native big data platform, private cloud cluster management, task scheduling, microservices, and multi-cloud architecture.'],
  ['Hewlett-Packard', 'Private cloud platform architecture, core modules, resource management, and infrastructure development.'],
  ['GPU pod tooling', 'vLLM-oriented deployment and GPU pod management experiments for agentic workloads.'],
];
---

<TerminalPage
  title="ai infrastructure"
  command="beixu@home:~$ cat /work/ai-infrastructure.md"
  description="Cloud-native AI infrastructure, resource scheduling, GPU management, and platform architecture."
>
  <section class="terminal-output work-detail">
    <p class="section-title">What this is</p>
    <p>
      Infrastructure work behind applied AI: cloud platforms, container systems,
      schedulers, GPU management, and deployment surfaces that let models and
      agentic workloads run reliably.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="detail-grid" aria-label="AI infrastructure cases">
    {systems.map(([name, detail]) => (
      <article>
        <p class="file-command">{name}</p>
        <p>{detail}</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </section>

  <section class="terminal-output">
    <p class="section-title">Core thread</p>
    <p>
      This is the base layer under the rest of the work: before agents,
      robotics, or clinical AI can be useful, they need reliable compute,
      orchestration, observability, and deployment paths.
    </p>
  </section>
</TerminalPage>
